.TH "vmw_msg_ioctl" 9 "vmw_msg_ioctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_msg_ioctl \- Sends and receveives a message to/from host from/to user-space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_msg_ioctl
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Identifies the drm device.
.IP "data" 12
Pointer to the ioctl argument.
.IP "file_priv" 12
Identifies the caller.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Sends a message from user-space to host.
Can also receive a result from host and return that to user-space.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative error code on error.
